; Regression test for issue #842: Automated postings with a tag = value match ignore the value (BZ#842)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/842
;
; The automated transaction rule uses tag("Category") == "food", which should only
; fire for transactions where the Category tag has the value "food". However, the
; bug causes the rule to fire for ALL transactions regardless of the tag value.
;
; Correct behavior: only Grocery Store (Category: food) triggers the auto rule.
;   Expected 2 auto postings (one per posting in that transaction), totaling $2.00
; Buggy behavior: Gas Station (Category: fuel) also triggers the rule.
;   Actual 4 auto postings, totaling $4.00

= tag("Category") == "food"
    Expenses:Food:Auto    $1.00
    Equity:AutoRules     -$1.00

2024/01/01 Grocery Store
    ; Category: food
    Expenses:Food    $10.00
    Assets:Cash

2024/01/02 Gas Station
    ; Category: fuel
    Expenses:Gas    $30.00
    Assets:Cash

test reg Expenses:Food:Auto
24-Jan-01 Grocery Store         Expenses:Food:Auto            $1.00        $1.00
                                Expenses:Food:Auto            $1.00        $2.00
24-Jan-02 Gas Station           Expenses:Food:Auto            $1.00        $3.00
                                Expenses:Food:Auto            $1.00        $4.00
end test
